The United States and Saudi Arabia are committed to strengthening their strategic partnership for the 21st century and promoting a peaceful Middle East. They plan to establish a Strategic Joint Consultative Group, which will meet annually to review areas of cooperation. Both countries aim to counter violent extremist messaging, disrupt terrorist financing, and enhance defense cooperation. They also seek to expand engagement with other regional countries and establish a robust regional security architecture. The partnership between the US and Saudi Arabia is based on trust, cooperation, and shared interests, and they are united in their efforts to confront common enemies and promote peace and prosperity.